As the answer contains a statement of figures, I will, with the hon. Member's permission, circulate it in the OFFICIAL REPORT.

Following is the answer:
The total number of public elementary schools in England and Wales on 31st March, 1935, was 20,854. Of these


9,207 were classified as Church of England school;

1,230 were classified as Roman Catholic schools;

316 were classified as Nonconformist schools;

13 were Jewish schools.
